Filtering tool

grep options pat path 

options
    -c pat	Count occurences of pattern
    -i	case insensitive search
	-w	match whole words
	-s	dont print access denied messages, etc
	-l  only list matching files
    -A# show # lines following match
    -r	recursive - search subdirectories
	-v  exclude match

    -o  print only matched part of line, matches on separate lines

	--exclude-dir=<dir>
	--exclude-dir={<dir>,<dir>}


Pattern Matching {{{1

Pattern matching with regex, not shell syntax
Will match anywhere on a liine

^/$   beginning/end of line (anchors)

Bracket expressions
    [abc]  match if any character 
    [^abc]  don't match if any 

Character classes
    [:upper:]

Find alternatives:
grep 'str1\|str2' filename

Repitition
    *   zero or more times
    extended 
        +       one or more 
        {n}     num of repititions
        {n,n}   range

Grouping
    ()  Enclose group.  Escape if not extended


Egrep
	Extended searching.  
	Quote expression and surround each regex with () and use:
	+	1=> occurances
	?	0<>1 occurances
	|	OR operator

	-f	Search for list of patterns in a file
	

Tips {{{1

Exclude blank lines and comments 
grep  "^[^# "]

excluding files under zsh
	grep -irl thing (*~*html)(.)

Match whole words, print each on separate line
    grep -oE '\w+' 

Alternatives {{{1

ack, ag, fzf


